Speculation has been rife for months that South African Reserve Bank’s (SARB’s) former deputy governor Daniel Mminele would be Absa’s next boss after Maria Ramos resigned last year, today it was confirmed, he will take over on the 15th January. However Viv Govender, a Senior Analyst at Rand Swiss reckons Mminele might not be the right fit. He believes someone from the IT or technology field would have been a better fit to deal with the structural changes in the banking industry that have seen new players, such as TymeBank and Bank Zero entering the market.  